Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: a worm can do things on it's own like it happened to genie.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: a worm can spread itself over network, and even wiping your 1 device can not get rid of it.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: today even the routers has openwrt in it. they are pretty secure, but some reouters with default pass can still invite worms to host as a backup for them.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: and router is 1 central point of home network

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: so you have to very careful

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: if you say no logs found etc. then most probably it's not incoming and then outgoing connecting, it's just outgoing via worm etc.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: there can be many types of complex worms and virus and what nots

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: windows is itself a worm/virus/*(&$(*%

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: no need of virus to have on it.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: and for corporate they give you a preinstalled virus. Windows. and enforce you to use it.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: if you get paranoid due to any X reason, sometimes it can do good to you, but also a disturbed mind can do an harm to self too.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: be patient, be cool, take deep breath if feel pressured. think twice before wiping, or encrypting your data, always make sure you have the backup or even multiple backups on site or off site, and then proceed with your security practices.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: make a schedule of your security cycle and stick to it and be punctual on these backups/cycles.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: make things semi automatic and not just fully automatic.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: and if you are anonymous, just be anonymous. there's nothing good with identity revealed over internet.
